-- Burundi Phone Companies to Build Fiber-Optic Network, Paper Says
-- B y   D e s i r e   N i m u b o n a
-- 2012-03-13T10:35:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/burundi-phone-companies-to-build-fiber-optic-network-paper-says.html
Five mobile-phone companies in
Burundi agreed to build a fiber-optic network in the East
African nation, Renouveau reported, citing Telecommunications
Minister Concilie Nibigira.  The companies include Leo Burundi, a unit of  Orascom
Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE) , state-owned Onatel, Econet Wireless
Holdings’ Burundian unit, along with Centre Burundais de
l’Internet and Africell, the Bujumbura-based newspaper said.  The World Bank will provide a $10.5 million grant to help
fund the project, while the phone companies will provide the
remaining $7.5 million needed to complete it, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Desire Nimubona in Bujumbura via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 